	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=203054><span id= >slinkytwf</span></a><br><span id=notbold>8 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent [3.33]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>Bloodfrenzy is a tremendous weapon.&nbsp;&nbsp;Mine is augmented with Anger III.  In one particular XP group in SolRo caves, I kept noticing our shaman kept typing, &quot;r, 1, 2, 3, 4, 5....&quot; in group chat.  It dawned on me that he was counting the number of aggro procs my BF was churning out.  I have never taken the time to parse it, but I estimate that with WA5 and 305 DEX, it fires at a rate of about 10 PPM, perhaps even higher.  I have no doubt that this is the absolute best 1-hand MT weapon available until you get to Plane of Time.  The BF procs so quickly that I usually can switch to a shield while engaging High-DPS mobs once aggro is established to avoid dual-wield ripostes.<br><br>As to the previous poster's lack of ambidexterity...  Dual-wielding on GoD mobs is very dangerous owing to insanely high riposte rates.  Most PoP bosses I have encountered (PoF access) are the same way.  Creating additional opportunities to get riposted, while having advantages in increasing your aggro and providing additional DPS, can also land you at your bind point if you eat an unlucky double 3K riposte.  Based on my experiences, I have NOT purchased ambidexterity either.  The addition of anger augmentations and /incite have allowed me to successfully hold aggro on everything I've faced so far (Tallon Zek excepted...) without increasing my attack rate beyond that allowed by normal haste capping.<br><br>Of course, anyone who really sets their mind to it can steal aggro from any warrior....<br><br><a href=HTTP://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=383991 target=akztarg> Aoifa De Danann</a>, League of Levity, The Rathe<br><br><em id=fs8>Edited, Mon Jul 19 01:52:50 2004</em></p>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
